-- Philippines May Import Additional Rice If La Nina Damages the Next Harvest
-- Luzi Ann Javier
-- 2010-07-09T07:19:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-09/philippines-may-import-additional-rice-if-la-nina-damages-the-next-harvest.html

          
          
             The Philippines may import rice if
the La Nina weather event damages the next harvest, Agriculture
Secretary Proceso Alcala said today in an interview.  
 La Nina is “always a cause for concern,” and the
Philippines will not be caught “flat footed,” Alcala said.  
